    <td>
      <center>
        <h1>Getting a Copy of <strong><em>Miriad</em></strong></h1>
      </center>
      <hr>
      <p>
      Please read the
      <a href="ftp://ftp.atnf.csiro.au/pub/software/miriad/DISCLAIMER">
      general disclaimer</a>.
      </p>

      <p>
      The following are available (ftp access):
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>The full <em>Miriad</em> distribution.</strong><br>
          This is available in
          <a href="ftp://ftp.atnf.csiro.au/pub/software/miriad/miriad.tar.Z">
          compressed</a> (11 Mbytes),
          <a href="ftp://ftp.atnf.csiro.au/pub/software/miriad/miriad.tar.gz">
          gzipped</a> (8 Mbytes) and
          <a href="ftp://ftp.atnf.csiro.au/pub/software/miriad/miriad.tar">
          plain</a> (22 Mbytes) tar formats.  <em>Note:</em> This distribution
          includes the Users and Programmer Guides, the installation notes and
          history of changes.
        </li>

        <li>
          <strong><a href=INSTALL.html>Installation, update and system guide
          </a></strong>, which includes
        </li>

        <ul>
          <li>
            <a href="INSTALL.html#installing">Instructions for installing
            <em>Miriad</em></a>
          </li>

          <li>
            <a href="INSTALL.html#updates">Getting regular updates</a>
          </li>

          <li>
            <a href="INSTALL.html#individual">Rebuilding individual tasks/subroutines</a>
          </li>

          <li>
            <a href="INSTALL.html#sysdep">System-dependent issues</a>
          </li>

          <li>
            <a href="INSTALL.html#special-cases">Special case tasks</a>
          </li>

          <li>
            <a href="INSTALL.html#structure">The structure of <em>Miriad</em>
            </a>
          </li>
        </ul>

        <li>
          <strong>The Users Guide.</strong><br>this is available in
          <a href="ftp://ftp.atnf.csiro.au/pub/software/miriad/userguide.ps.Z">
          compressed</a> (800 kbytes) and
          <a href="ftp://ftp.atnf.csiro.au/pub/software/miriad/userguide.ps.gz">
          gzipped</a> postscript forms, configured for A4 paper size.  US letter
          paper size versions
          (<a href="ftp://ftp.atnf.csiro.au/pub/software/miriad/userguide_US.ps.Z">compressed
          </a> and
          <a href="ftp://ftp.atnf.csiro.au/pub/software/miriad/userguide_US.ps.gz">gzipped
          </a> postscript) are also available.
        </li>

        <li>
          <strong>The Programmers Guide.</strong><br>  This is available in
          <a href="ftp://ftp.atnf.csiro.au/pub/software/miriad/progguide.ps.Z">
          compressed</a> (180 kbytes) and
          <a href="ftp://ftp.atnf.csiro.au/pub/software/miriad/progguide.ps.gz">
          gzipped</a> postscript forms, configured for A4 paper.  US letter
          paper size versions
          (<a href="ftp://ftp.atnf.csiro.au/pub/software/miriad/progguide_US.ps.Z">
          compressed</a> and
          <a href="ftp://ftp.atnf.csiro.au/pub/software/miriad/progguide_US.ps.gz">
          gzipped</a> postscript) are also available.  This manual is rather
          out of date.
        </li>

        <li>
          <strong>a
          <a href="ftp://ftp.atnf.csiro.au/pub/software/miriad/changes.txt">
          History of changes</a>.  </strong><br>This is in text form, giving
          changes from the ancient to the recent.  This reflects the the
          current distribution.
        </li>

        <li>
          <strong>A directory of
          <a href="ftp://ftp.atnf.csiro.au/pub/software/miriad/bindir/">some
          statically-linked tasks.</a></strong>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <em>Miriad</em> makes use of the following libraries:
      <ul>
        <li>
          The <a href="http://astro.caltech.edu/~tjp/pgplot/">PGPLOT
          library</a> (essential for <em>Miriad's</em> plotting tasks).  This
          is included in the <em>Miriad</em> distribution.
        </li>

        <li>
          Generally PGPLOT needs the libX11.a library.  Additionally two
          <em>Miriad</em> utilities need the Athena widgets library.
        </li>

        <li>
          The ATNF
          <a href="http://www.atnf.csiro.au/computing/software/rpfits.html">
          RPFITS library</a>, which is only used by the task ATLOD.  This
          library is needed to load raw ATNF data.  The binaries of this (for
          some architectures!) are available in the
          <a href="ftp://ftp.atnf.csiro.au/pub/software/miriad/bindir/">
          statically-linked binaries</a> area.
        </li>

        <li>
          The
          <a href="ftp://prep.ai.mit.edu/pub/gnu/readline/readline-4.0.tar.gz">
          GNU readline library</a>, which is an optional library to give the
          <em>Miriad</em> shell command-line editting ability.
        </li>
      </ul>
      Some additional software, of interest to BIMA users, is also available
      <a href="ftp://ftp.atnf.csiro.au/pub/software/miriad/bima.tar">from
      here</a> (the ATNF does not support this).
      <p>
      A memo on the relative performance of <em>Miriad</em> on different
      machines is <a href="http://bima.astro.umd.edu/memo/memo81.ps">
      available from BIMA</a>.
    </td>
  </tr>
</table>
</body>
